14 SECTION 3.3. Article 56A of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
15 adding a new section to read:
16 "§ 58-56A-55. Health benefit plan requirements applicable.
17 (a) All requirements relating to the coverage of prescription drugs and pharmacy services
18 under this Chapter that apply to health benefit plans are applicable to pharmacy benefits managers
19 in the same way they are applicable to an insurer.
20 (b) Article 63 of this Chapter, Unfair Trade Practices, is applicable to a pharmacy benefits
21 manager in the same manner as it is applicable to an insurer."
22 SECTION 3.4. G.S. 58-56A-21 reads as rewritten:
23 "§ 58-56A-21. Claims data provided to health benefit plan.Duties owed to contracted
24 insurers.
25 (a) Fiduciary Duty. – A pharmacy benefits manager has a fiduciary duty to act in good
26 faith and fair dealing in the performance of all of its contractual duties, including all of the
27 following:
28 (1) Controlling costs.
29 (2) Acting in the best interest of the insureds under the health benefit plans offered
30 by the insurer with which the pharmacy benefits manager has a contract.
31 (3) Acting with prudence and passing through any rebates or discounts the
32 pharmacy benefits manager received related to covered benefits bought and
33 paid for with the contracted insurer's assets or funds.
34 (4) Avoiding self-dealing and conflicts of interest.
35 (b) Claims Data Requests. – Upon the request of an insurer offering a health benefit plan
36 that contracts with a pharmacy benefits manager, the pharmacy benefits manager shall provide
37 the insurer with claims data that reflects the total amount the insurer paid to the pharmacy benefits
38 manager under the health benefit plan for a specified outpatient prescription drug, including the
39 ingredient cost and the dispensing fee. The pharmacy benefits manager shall also provide the
40 cost that it paid for the specified outpatient prescription drug, including the ingredient cost and
41 the dispensing fee."
42 SECTION 3.5. Sections 3.1 and 3.2 of this Part are effective October 1, 2025. The
43 remainder of this Part is effective when it becomes law.
