20 REFILLS
21 SECTION 5.1.(a) G.S. 90-85.3 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
22 "(i2) "Independent pharmacy" has the same meaning as in G.S. 58-51-37."
23 SECTION 5.1.(b) G.S. 90-85.3A reads as rewritten:
24 "§ 90-85.3A. Practice of pharmacy.
25 …
26 (e) A pharmacy has a professional responsibility to offer complete pharmaceutical
27 services to meet the needs of patients."
28 SECTION 5.1.(c) Article 4A of Chapter 90 of the General Statutes is amended by
29 adding a new section to read:
30 "§ 90-85.21E. Independent pharmacy prescriptions.
31 (a) An independent pharmacy may decline to fill or refill a prescription if that act would
32 directly result in an unbearable cost to the independent pharmacy, provided that the independent
33 pharmacy meets the requirements of subsection (b) of this section. If the independent pharmacy
34 cannot find a pharmacy to accept the referral without causing harm to the patient, then the
35 independent pharmacy must fill the prescription.
36 (b) If the independent pharmacy elects to decline to fill or refill a prescription under
37 subsection (a) of this section, then, prior to declining to fill or refill a prescription, the
38 independent pharmacy shall refer the prescription and patient to another pharmacy that is equally
39 convenient for the patient to fill or refill the prescription in the same manner without the patient
40 suffering any harm. The independent pharmacy may refer the prescription to a pharmacy that
41 only provides centralized pharmacy services in this State through the mail or remote medication
42 order processing services subject to the Board's rules if the independent pharmacy makes a
43 determination the provision of pharmaceutical services through the mail does not harm the
44 patient."
45 SECTION 5.2. No later than October 1, 2025, the North Carolina Board of Pharmacy
46 shall adopt rules to implement this Part.
47 SECTION 5.3. Section 5.1 of this Part becomes effective October 1, 2025. The
48 remainder of this Part is effective when it becomes law.
