8 PART VII. PHARMACY BENEFITS MANAGER AFFILIATES
9 SECTION 7.1. G.S. 58-56A-20 reads as rewritten:
10 "§ 58-56A-20. Pharmacy benefits manager affiliate disclosure; sharing of data.affiliates.
11 (a) A pharmacy benefits manager shall not, in any way that is prohibited by the Health
12 Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 (HIPAA), transfer or share records relative
13 to prescription information containing patient-identifiable and prescriber-identifiable data to a
14 pharmacy benefits manager affiliate.
15 (b) A pharmacy benefits manager shall not reimburse a pharmacy or pharmacist in this
16 State an amount less than the amount that the pharmacy benefits manager reimburses a pharmacy
17 benefits manager affiliate for providing the same pharmacist services or same prescription drug.
18 In determining the amount of the reimbursement for the purposes of this section, the amount shall
19 be calculated on a per-unit basis using the same generic product identifier or generic code number
20 and shall reflect all drug manufacturer's rebates, all direct and indirect administrative fees, and
21 any other cost-savings or discounts that may be given related to the drug or services. A violation
22 of this subsection is an unfair trade practice under Article 63 of this Chapter and under
23 G.S. 75-1.1 and is subject to all of the enforcement and penalty provisions of an unfair trade
24 practice under this Chapter and under Article 1 of Chapter 75 of the General Statutes."
25 SECTION 7.2. This Part becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to
26 pharmacist services or prescription drugs dispensed on or after that date.
